They Thought The War Was Over.

$54,000,000 In Gold Changed Their Minds.

No-one in their right minf even hoped to get away with the stealing of $54 million of gold intended to free American prisoners-of-war, nor with teh brutal killing of billionaire industrialist and U.S. Senator, John Point.

No-one, except the sadistic Vietnam war deserter Jeff Slater - but the C.I.A. are brought in to make sure he won't.

"In Gold We Trust" - a gripping story of greed, murder, deceit and revenge.
